Explanation:

The problem requires finding the number of paths connecting each garden to itself. We can use nested loops to iterate through all paths and count the number of paths connecting each garden to itself. Since there are n gardens, the time complexity is O(n). The space complexity is O(1) since we only use a single integer array to store the count of paths. The energy implications are low as the algorithm only requires a small amount of computational resources.

